	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Get these.&nbsp;&nbsp;They drop off holgresh Elders in wakening lands.  Unlimited charges of eye of zomm.  Monk, as well as any class can R-click the item in inventory (hope they don't nerf it)  The trick is, while FD (feign death) the eye will not aggro a mob on the monk.  It just gets killed and that's it.  Easy to split mobs like this. alSo you get 30 sec of aggro free scouting, and can pull a mob out of your line of sight if you want.  If anything goes wrong, you're far enought away to FD without getting hit as well.  A level 60 monk in my guild traded me a journeyman's walking stick (Very nice Staff) for these.  He loves em. =)<br><br>Gobo<br>&lt;Heroic Few&gt;<br>Morell Thule<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
