	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>679 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At 33-38 I hunted a lot in The Overthere.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's a big, busy zone, with a number of good spots to camp.  Usually easy to find groups, good exp, and your feign death keeps you safe when the roaming dragoons show up.  Frontier mountains is a bit light for you, I think.  You can also hunt cougars in Iceclad - my brother with his ranger and I with my monk were fear-kiting cougars for incredible experience (a blue every 4-5 cats) in mid-thirties.  You can also fight High Keep for another couple levels, if you want, though the xp starts to slow down at 34-35 - I spent a lot of time mid 20s to low 30s in HK.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro </p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
