	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.44]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hands work fine during your lower levels; however, as you approach your twenties, the quality of your hands as a weapon diminishes vs. the MOBs you're likely to be fighting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eventually, when you get to a HIGH (50+) level, hands catch back up, especially when you add the Celestial Fists epic weapon.  However, without the Celestial Fists, most monks use 2HB at a high level, and even good 1HB weapons will still beat fists.<br><br>Most monks stop using their fists as their main attack at some point in their mid-teens or early twenties (untwinked).  Once you have some cash, buy the best weapon you can afford and put it in your primary hand.  Continuing to use your fist offhand is just fine -- you can get a bit more damage with a second weapon, but it's probably not be the best value (get armor instead), and you'll keep up your training in H2H as well.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
