	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>679 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.47]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Near as I've ever been able to tell, 4 AGI gets you one point of AC.&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't know if level affects that - haven't checked it in a while.  The key thing to consider is that it takes a lot of Agi to get a little AC - and even if you burn 15 stat points on Agi you're only getting 4 AC for it.  Considering that at high levels there seems to be a multiplying effect when you equip AC gear (If I equip a AC 7 piece, my AC goes up 10 or 11 - never saw an explanation for it though) the 3 or 4 AC you get from skill points doesn't seem to be a good return on investment here.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br></p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
