	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.78]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok, for convenience a druid is good, and they do have some nice spells to work with.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, for pure maximum fighting efficiency a shaman would be best.  Probably barbarian, as that would give you similar faction situations to start.<br><br>The shaman spell line is ideally suited to a monk, and I prefer them even to clerics now to pair with.  Buff me up, keep quickness and regen refreshed, slow the mobs and ROCK.  Plus, they get SOW early, which is very nice for outdoor pulling and travelling.  With their ability to cannibalize, if played right, there will be almost no downtime and they should never be OOM.  If needed, you can bind their wounds while they cannibalize.<br><br>At lower levels, a Cleric might be better (not sure, didn't really start appreciating shaman-power until my thirties), but in the long run a shaman is the best partner for a monk.</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
