	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99243244096461>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=99243244096461>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99243244096461>RE: Epic</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99243244096461#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 13th 7:40 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.24]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The monk Epic is the Celestial Fists -- a H2H weapon (basically uber-gloves).&nbsp;&nbsp;The path to these is long and involved, but the beauty of the Monk Epic series of quests is you can start at level ONE.  You will always have something to work on with the monk Epic Quest path.<br><br>Start by getting your white sash or headband from your starting guild -- Sashes in Freeport, Headbands in Qeynos.  Eventually you will need to get the highest level in each -- Purple Headband and Red Sash.  If you are trying to do these as you go, you can complete these quests by level 35 grouped or level 41 solo (roughly -- will depend on your equipment, quality of groupmates, etc.).<br><br>I *just* got my purple headband tonight -- finally killed that bastard High Priest Zaharn in Permafrost.  He's far and away the hardest MOB you have to kill in the headband/sash series.  He has a HUGE amount of mana.  During my fight with him tonight, he managed to cast Wrath 5 times, and Greater Heal himself 7 times.  Once he was finally OOM, he dropped like a brick of course -- heh heh.  Could I have *bought* his drop in EC? Sure, but getting the items myself is a matter of pride.<br><br>In any event, the next step is the Robe of the Lost Circle -- a VERY nice chest piece, and typically quested for in the mid-40s.  You will need to turn in your sash and headband, plus get a few more items to obtain this.<br><br>After that, it's the Robe of the Whistling Fists, an even better chest piece, and something typically quested for in the low 50s.<br><br>Finally, once you have this item, you can get your Epic -- but you will need 2 to 4 groups (depending on level) of good friends to help.  There are quite a few major battles to deal with on this, and it's completely impossible to solo.<br><br>For good walkthroughs on all the Monk quests, see the guides at www.monkly-business.com<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
