	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=63650><span id= >Kexel</span></a><br><span id=notbold>18 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Poor? I am surprised, go to the Field of Bones, there you can find just about everything that you need to start amassing a fortune... a lot skeles in Kurn's tower and always high levels looking for bone chips will buy a stack from you for 3-5pp.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can kill a multitude of creatures (always a large number of creatures compared to players) that will give you silver/gold, look for low level skeles carrying shields the shields will sell for about 1 pp each, also all of the spiders carry a nice amount of silks and can be either sold to players or merchants for good profits.<br><br>As far as your skill question, make sure you are fighting blues or better to work on that skill other wise it will take forever... One thing I noticed when I start a skill that I haven't developed much is that it is slow to start off. I would advise pumping it up with skill points (if you have some to spare) and expect it to start raising faster once you hit skill 1hb(20-30ish)<br><br>Good luck to you.<br><br>Kexel Spineweaver<br>Monk of the 24th Fist<br>Saryrn Server<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
